<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99576873650645></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99576873650645><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99576873650645>RE: Where to get through 53 to 55</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99576873650645#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jul 21st 10:25 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sure it is. I've seen the mid 50's tackled in a few days of hardcore leveling with a good group. <br><br>Get some friends around your level with a similiar goal (not more then one or two levels either way above or below) and arrange to meet everynight in a predsignated location. <br><br>Expect to put in 5-8 hours a night for 3-6 nights, but your levels CAN be hit in a week, it just takes a good group. By the second day you'll either be a good group... or you'll be dead. And if you made it to the low 50's, i'm guessing the former. Crappy players don't make it to the 50's often.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
