<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99479033912519></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99479033912519><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99479033912519>RE: Iskar</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99479033912519#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 10th 2:38 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are several newbie areas in the various zones that border Cabilis (East and West), but by far the most popular is Field of Bone (FoB). Your initial bind point is there, so when you die (and a low lvl shaman will die a lot), you're close to your hunting ground.&nbsp;&nbsp;Services in East Cabilis are close also.  I would concentrate on killing scorpions and scaled wolf pups (there are quests related to these mobs; search this website for info on Curscale Armor Quest and Scorpion Pincer Quest).  Hunt these through lvl 4, then head to "The Pit" located in the middle of FoB.  You can easily hunt there though your mid-teens.<br><br>Concerning weapons: As a shaman in a GROUP, you normally will not engage a mob in direct combat. Your job essentailly is buff, heal and/or dot. Having said this, there are a series of quests Shaman Skull Quests) related to the improvement of the 1HB weapon given to you when you create the character. Try to loot or buy a cheap spear and work on piercing also.<br><br>As far as travel, as a shaman you will eventually get Invisibility, which will help you a lot.  Also there are places you can trade and bank as an Iksar. I have a lvl 31 Iksar shaman camped next to a friendly ogre in Lake Rathetear at the moment. Plus, you will be able to summon food and water. So, yeah, you won't be able to enter the paladin's guild in Qeynos anytime soon, but being Iksar is not as big a hassle as some folks makeit out to be. (My main character is a lvl 35 Iksar monk.) You might want to see if your friend can come to Kunark to hunt--great hunting there at all levels.<br><br>Anyway, hope this info helped and good luck.<br>   <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
