	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just a few things to add.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>1. Yes the testment is worth it, I got mine at lvl 20 or so, and still use it when I'm in mana mod at lvl 50. <br>2. Shaman can melee at least till lvl 50.  Of your weapons skills 2hd is by far the most important.  You should use 2hb's anytime you intend to melee.  When fully buffed I often hit for over 100 hp of damage with my 2hb.  Shaman can and should melee whenever soloing or with a small group.  If your group has less then 3 melee class they have much more magic than melee and odds are you can help the group by meleeing as well as by casting buffs and slow. Are you a pure tank? No. Can you do meaningful damage? Yes.  Using a good 2hb I could do more damage meleeing that I could with my best dot until lvl 49. <br>I carry a few items with me, that i use to switch between melee mode and mana mode.  The Testment is still one of them.   <br><br>On killing the guard for the book, forget about root. Just slow, dot, melee.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
