	   <tr><td colspan=2>You're at that kind of awkward stage/lvl where maybe you want to consider doing more group than solo.&nbsp;&nbsp;For your lvl, full banded armor isn't bad at all (though you might want to consider trying to get your hands on a bloodstained tunic).  The jump from the wis jewelry you have now to the next step up is a pricey one.  What you have for now is fine.  I would, however, consider getting a faster weapon.  Bloodforge hammer is okay, but it is painfully slow.  At your lvl, the 2hb, I preferred was a glowing wooden crook (dropped by Lockjaw in Oasis), and you can pick one up for around 40pp (ballpark).  If you are soloing, it's important to have a weapon that hits both hard and fast.  [for those uber punks out there who may have some other weapon suggestions, I'm trying to be realistic and fall within this poster's financial abilities]<br><br>If I was you, I'd be in Lake of Ill Omen grouping for awesome exp.  My experience is that healing classes do not ever have a problem finding groups there (and honestly you'll not have problems finding groups simply because you can SoW).<br><br>Good luck!<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>54 Barbarian Shaman (Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>35 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
